# Phone number display

When showing phone numbers in **reports, tables, or read-only views**, always format them with `formatDisplayPhone` from `frontend/src/passengerDisplay.ts`.

- Target format: `(xxx) xxx-xxxx` for 10-digit US numbers
- Never show decimal artifacts from spreadsheet imports (e.g. `5551234567.0`)

```tsx
// ✅ Display (report cell, client table, modal detail)
<td>{formatDisplayPhone(client.phone) ?? "—"}</td>

// ❌ Raw stored value in a view
<td>{client.phone ?? "—"}</td>
```

**Input fields stay raw.** Do not auto-format while the user is typing or editing. Bind inputs to the stored string (`value={form.phone}`) and only format on read-only display and export output.

Use `formatPassengerContact` when combining email and phone in a single line.
